{
  "texts": [
    "Research in this area aims to create more efficient and interpretable LLMs.",
    "Sparse expert models can be particularly beneficial in scenarios where computational resources are limited, such as edge devices or real-time applications.",
    "Additionally, the sparsity of these models often makes them more interpretable, addressing concerns about the \"black box\" nature of LLMs.",
    "The rise of sparse expert models signifies a shift towards more resource-efficient and interpretable LLM solutions, paving the way for their application in a wider range of real-world settings.",
    "This survey undertakes a comprehensive examination of recent advancements in Large Language Models (LLMs), offering a detailed overview of prominent models in both industrial and academic domains."
  ]
}